WEBVTT

00:34.018 --> 00:37.382
Welcome back to our study of Proverbs.

00:38.403 --> 00:43.148
And again, we're in chapter seven, but we're closing in on being finished.

00:44.930 --> 00:50.377
We're going to start in verse 22 and read all the way to 27.

00:52.078 --> 00:52.319
Right.

00:53.200 --> 01:02.290
Suddenly he follows her as an ox goes to the slaughter or as one in the fetters, in fetters to the discipline of a fool.

01:02.850 --> 01:11.020
until an arrow pierces through his liver, as a bird hastens to the snare, so he does not know that it will cost him his life.

01:12.221 --> 01:16.206
Now therefore my sons listen to me and pay attention to the words of my mouth.

01:17.167 --> 01:19.810
Do not let your heart turn aside to her ways.

01:20.511 --> 01:22.213
Do not stray into her paths.

01:22.934 --> 01:28.580
For many are the victims she has cast down, and numerous are all her slain.

01:29.361 --> 01:30.162
Her house,

01:30.818 --> 01:35.705
is the way of shield descending to the chambers of death.

01:37.227 --> 01:38.408
Let's go to the Lord in prayer.

01:42.494 --> 01:48.422
Father, we come before you as always and only in the name of your son.

01:51.546 --> 01:54.831
We boast of no righteousness of our own.

01:56.393 --> 01:57.074
We have none.

01:59.458 --> 02:18.341
Our boast is in Jesus Christ, His perfect life, His death, His resurrection and power, His being seated once again at your right hand.

02:20.384 --> 02:26.812
Father, we praise You, we worship You, and we realize that we are Yours because of You.

02:27.793 --> 02:28.754
We remain

02:28.834 --> 02:37.287
yours because of you, that you are our salvation from Alpha to Omega.

02:38.829 --> 02:55.634
Lord, I pray that you would use this time to truly instill in these young people the fear of the Lord and the deadly nature of sin.

02:59.682 --> 03:00.603
in Jesus' name.

03:01.564 --> 03:01.885
Amen.

03:04.788 --> 03:09.534
So when we look in verse 22, we see that suddenly He follows her.

03:10.175 --> 03:11.036
Let's just review.

03:11.096 --> 03:17.925
You'll follow somebody, yourself, the world, or God through following His Word.

03:18.546 --> 03:20.228
You're going to follow someone.

03:20.308 --> 03:28.338
As the preacher says, you're going to be a slave to someone, to yourself, to some other man or woman,

03:28.770 --> 03:32.235
or society, or you're going to be a slave to God.

03:33.177 --> 03:36.422
There's no way you're getting out of this without following someone.

03:37.203 --> 03:40.729
And so you must decide whom you're going to follow.

03:41.149 --> 03:56.914
And suddenly here is very important because it indicates that even though his life has been described in many verses, or his wanderings in many verses, his sudden destruction is just described into

03:58.082 --> 04:08.592
and that you could live a wholesome life, but with one bad decision to destroy that life entirely.

04:09.894 --> 04:11.916
He follows her and it's deadly.

04:12.776 --> 04:21.145
As an ox goes to the slaughter, ox go to slaughter because they don't know they're going to slaughter a fool in fetters.

04:23.146 --> 04:24.548
Here's what you need to realize.

04:25.269 --> 04:26.770
He's in those fetters.

04:27.330 --> 04:34.660
In this case, not necessarily because he's a criminal, he's committed some act against the law of man.

04:34.741 --> 04:46.577
He's in the fetters because he's a fool, because he has refused to either learn from God or listen to what he has learned from God.

04:47.318 --> 04:55.410
He's also like a bird hastening to a snare, verse 23, which doesn't say much for the sense that he has.

04:56.002 --> 05:01.329
And just let me say this again, young person, you are not born with wisdom.

05:01.849 --> 05:03.611
You are not born with great sins.

05:05.093 --> 05:10.500
You learn these things as you mature, as you're taught the word of God.

05:12.602 --> 05:23.976
It is also the responsibility of the wise, the older and the wiser who have studied God's word to communicate God's word to the younger and the more foolish.

05:24.837 --> 05:25.298
Okay.

05:25.762 --> 05:28.847
Now, so he's like an ox to the slaughter.

05:28.947 --> 05:31.691
He's like a fool and fetters going to judgment.

05:31.711 --> 05:35.256
He's like a bird that's about to be captured in a snare.

05:35.316 --> 05:38.481
That's where he's walking and he doesn't know it.

05:38.841 --> 05:40.343
He doesn't know he's in danger yet.

05:41.265 --> 05:49.317
And then look at verse 23, until an arrow pierces through his liver.

05:50.418 --> 05:55.666
And I've, I've written here, he did not realize

05:56.130 --> 06:00.675
that what he thought would bring him joy would actually cost in his life.

06:03.478 --> 06:24.882
Again, remember, it's like putting, if cows could read, putting a huge sign out in front of a slaughterhouse, you know, for a good time, inquire within.

06:26.498 --> 06:30.443
And they think, Oh, I want a good time until they go in.

06:30.503 --> 06:37.492
And when they go in and the gate is shut behind them, then the slaughter begins.

06:37.572 --> 06:39.435
Now it says it'll cost him his life.

06:39.475 --> 06:40.797
So we're talking about this young man.

06:41.097 --> 06:42.759
How will it cost him his life?

06:43.500 --> 06:51.270
I want, I want you to see, uh, first of all, in 634 and 35, let's just look for a moment at that.

06:53.433 --> 06:54.034
It says,

06:55.394 --> 07:00.282
For jealousy enrages a man and he will not spare in the day of vengeance.

07:00.682 --> 07:06.912
He will not accept any ransom, nor will he be satisfied, though you give him many gifts."

07:06.932 --> 07:17.129
This is talking about a man whose wife has committed adultery and his anger against the man with whom she committed adultery.

07:17.609 --> 07:18.851
That he will not spare him.

07:19.793 --> 07:21.435
He will take vengeance.

07:21.836 --> 07:23.058
He will kill him.

07:23.458 --> 07:27.704
And there's nothing that the man can do to appease his anger.

07:28.825 --> 07:34.052
And what we learn from this is that this young man, he's doing that very thing.

07:36.215 --> 07:37.436
He's committing adultery.

07:38.117 --> 07:44.265
And so his life will be destroyed by the violence of another man.

07:44.786 --> 07:50.834
Now we can take that generally and just say sin kills, sin kills,

07:51.170 --> 07:56.917
And there are some sins that you can commit for which there's no reparation.

07:57.558 --> 07:59.540
There's no way to turn back the clock.

07:59.800 --> 08:01.262
There's no way to fix it.

08:02.484 --> 08:07.149
I've talked to so many people in prison, so many people on drugs, things like that.

08:07.169 --> 08:14.098
And they said, only if I could go back, I wouldn't do that again.

08:14.118 --> 08:16.721
I would not take that drug again.

08:16.861 --> 08:17.682
I would not.

08:17.826 --> 08:20.489
get drunk and kill someone in a car.

08:20.969 --> 08:22.070
I would not murder.

08:22.210 --> 08:22.711
I would not.

08:22.811 --> 08:27.636
If only I could go back, but you can not go back.

08:28.216 --> 08:35.083
So one way in which this young man's life could be ruined is that it's just destroyed.

08:35.944 --> 08:36.785
But there's another.

08:37.225 --> 08:39.107
Look in 633.

08:39.227 --> 08:46.514
He talks about the adult where and it says wounds and disgrace he will find and his reproach

08:46.722 --> 08:48.124
will not be blotted out.

08:50.107 --> 08:56.435
He will never, never regain the respect of others.

08:58.198 --> 09:01.442
His reproach will not be blotted out.

09:01.843 --> 09:06.910
Now, we need to forgive, but there is a reality here.

09:07.291 --> 09:15.602
You can commit certain sins and that shame of that sin, at least in society, will be on

09:15.682 --> 09:16.663
you forever.

09:17.144 --> 09:26.475
And it can, certain sins restrict or make it impossible that you ever do certain things in the ministry.

09:27.477 --> 09:36.047
Yes, you can commit certain sins so that you're never allowed into the ministry or you're not allowed back into the ministry.

09:36.608 --> 09:38.590
And so how does sin ruin us?

09:39.031 --> 09:40.072
Well, it can kill us.

09:40.793 --> 09:44.658
It can physically kill us, but it can also destroy

09:44.898 --> 09:54.693
reputation and sometime that reputation can be regained and sometimes it can never be regained again.

09:54.733 --> 10:13.042
Now I want to read something that I wrote down here and I remember this we we had a cattle ranch and I mean we had a lot of cattle and sometimes we would take them to the slaughterhouse and I wrote here when we took cattle to the slaughterhouse and

10:13.506 --> 10:19.896
They seemed unaware of their fate until we unloaded them at the slaughterhouse.

10:19.956 --> 10:20.837
I can remember this.

10:21.518 --> 10:22.359
We would load them.

10:23.080 --> 10:25.424
We had certain loading pens and things like that.

10:25.464 --> 10:33.997
And we'd push them with the horses into those loading pens, push them into the chute and then up the chute into the trucks or into the trailers.

10:35.319 --> 10:42.930
And although they didn't like it, there wasn't this look in their eyes of almost being hysterical.

10:43.458 --> 10:44.720
of being terrified.

10:45.861 --> 10:47.043
They were just bothered.

10:47.103 --> 10:48.024
They didn't want to be there.

10:49.746 --> 11:02.663
But when you drew close to the slaughterhouse, when you got there and there were animals being killed, there was almost a wildness that would be in their eyes because they would smell the blood.

11:03.605 --> 11:06.869
It seemed and and they just changed.

11:07.470 --> 11:08.531
They could get dangerous.

11:08.591 --> 11:10.674
They could run through.

11:10.946 --> 11:13.249
offense, they could leap over a wall.

11:13.810 --> 11:15.992
They knew there was danger.

11:17.154 --> 11:18.836
And that's what's so sad about sin.

11:19.457 --> 11:22.180
At first, you kind of just, everything's good.

11:23.021 --> 11:30.771
There's nothing to be terrified of and nothing to be afraid of until it clamps down, until the consequences come.

11:31.672 --> 11:39.282
Now, another thing it says in verse 23, until an arrow pierces his liver.

11:40.098 --> 11:51.329
Now, to some of you, that might not mean a whole lot, but to someone who's been hunting since he was a little boy, it means quite a bit.

11:54.112 --> 12:09.106
When you're hunting with a bow and arrow, and you're hunting a deer, or even with a gun, when you take the shot, and then, you know, you wait maybe 30 minutes because you almost spooked animal,

12:09.602 --> 12:37.842
if it's wounded you wait 30 minutes and then you start looking for a blood trail and when you find that blood trail and it's extraordinarily dark dark dark dark that blood it's not red it's just really dark you know pretty much that you've hit the liver now you have hit that liver you know it's going to cause severe bleeding

12:38.114 --> 12:40.437
And you know that animal's going to die.

12:41.478 --> 12:46.323
I mean, you get, you pierce that liver, you send an arrow, a broad head through that liver.

12:47.104 --> 12:51.789
Now you may have to track for a while, but that animal is going to die.

12:52.069 --> 12:53.111
They're not going to recover.

12:53.551 --> 12:55.693
But here's something else that you need to understand.

12:56.755 --> 13:01.240
When you hit that liver, sometimes it takes a long time for the animal to die.

13:02.361 --> 13:07.026
And so what he's talking about here is not only a death,

13:07.682 --> 13:11.606
but a slow and agonizing death.

13:12.527 --> 13:13.908
And that's what he's saying here.

13:14.689 --> 13:24.058
He says, until an arrow pierces his liver, sin is deadly.

13:25.780 --> 13:28.482
But there's a difference between sin and a broad head.

13:30.064 --> 13:36.530
You get shot with a broad head, you're probably going to die, but you're going to die physically and that death may be temporal.

13:37.570 --> 13:42.216
if you're Christian, but sin kills eternally.

13:43.858 --> 13:48.544
There are people as much as unpleasant as this truth is.

13:48.604 --> 13:49.625
You need to understand.

13:50.487 --> 14:05.746
There are people in hell who will remain in hell forever, not because of a broad head, not because of a bullet or a bomb, but because of sin, because of sin.

14:09.730 --> 14:29.070
You know, sometimes when I study something like this, if I could just reach through the camera and grab you by both of your ears and pull you up close to me and say, are you listening to me?

14:31.893 --> 14:36.658
You know, I used to have a friend, a big old dude.

14:37.090 --> 14:38.471
and he would always say things.

14:38.531 --> 14:39.692
It ain't no baby's game.

14:41.054 --> 14:43.156
And it's not.

14:44.317 --> 14:46.519
Like I said before, a few lessons back.

14:47.600 --> 14:52.685
This is a matter of life and of death, but it's even worse than that.

14:53.025 --> 14:54.446
It's even more severe than that.

14:55.307 --> 14:58.610
It's a matter of heaven and hell.

14:58.630 --> 15:01.713
What we're talking about here is eternity.

15:04.836 --> 15:06.578
What we're talking about here

15:06.690 --> 15:08.892
is eternity.

15:10.874 --> 15:15.959
And there are certain things that you should fear.

15:18.642 --> 15:22.286
Now, when we talk about fearing God, that's important.

15:22.306 --> 15:31.595
But what that means is a deep and abiding reference because of who he is.

15:32.216 --> 15:34.738
And not only that, because of what he can do,

15:35.874 --> 15:39.359
to you even should fear him.

15:40.460 --> 15:43.544
He is good, but you should fear him.

15:45.567 --> 15:47.790
But with sin, it's something quite different.

15:49.192 --> 15:50.734
With God, he's consistent.

15:51.575 --> 15:52.256
He's faithful.

15:52.697 --> 15:53.357
He's good.

15:54.058 --> 15:55.641
And he's always going to be that way.

15:56.982 --> 15:59.906
Sin is fickle and deadly.

16:00.227 --> 16:05.714
And all it wants to do is ruin you, is destroy you.

16:06.498 --> 16:18.495
And just out there, I want you to think about, when you walk out there in that world, that's not, you don't just have to deal with your own flesh that fights against God.

16:19.837 --> 16:26.106
But you have to deal with almost an entire world that is trying to influence you to leave God.

16:26.186 --> 16:34.418
And then beyond even that, there is one called the devil who is like a roaring lion

16:34.530 --> 16:42.341
Seeking whom he may devour, devour, devour.

16:44.944 --> 16:51.553
I remember one time we had these feral dogs that were on getting our cattle.

16:52.434 --> 16:56.039
And I can remember one day my dad was driving in the field.

16:56.320 --> 17:03.890
I was little boy and we saw one of our calves being drug away.

17:04.994 --> 17:09.098
And my dad, he went right for the dog with the truck.

17:09.118 --> 17:17.186
And what was astounding is how fierce those dogs were, how they were trying to rip that calf apart.

17:17.526 --> 17:19.368
And even they didn't fear the truck.

17:19.488 --> 17:21.230
They didn't fear anything.

17:21.750 --> 17:25.013
They were vicious and vile and deadly.

17:25.333 --> 17:28.797
That is sin and you need to understand it.

17:29.097 --> 17:34.322
So when someone's tempting you with something that seems to be harmless, it's not.

17:34.818 --> 17:36.280
You need to see it for what it is.

17:36.320 --> 17:37.482
You need to unmask it.

17:37.843 --> 17:38.463
It's evil.

17:39.084 --> 17:39.926
It's dangerous.

17:40.106 --> 17:45.394
It's deadly and it can ruin you in this life and ruin you in the next.

17:46.055 --> 17:48.819
You say, Brother Paul, why are you harping on this?

17:49.039 --> 17:50.281
Because it's true.

17:54.187 --> 17:58.814
I've had to travel a big part of the world and some pretty ugly places.

18:00.937 --> 18:01.458
Every

18:01.858 --> 18:03.680
thing that's wrong with this world.

18:03.941 --> 18:13.133
Everything, every injustice, every hurt, every crime, every tear, it all can be traced back to one thing, sin.

18:16.137 --> 18:25.891
Sin is like a wild animal, a rabid, hungry, wild animal, right outside your tent.

18:27.713 --> 18:31.218
Not outside your stone fortress, right outside your tent.

18:32.034 --> 18:34.979
And its desire is to devour you.

18:36.261 --> 18:39.365
And that is not in any way an exaggeration.

18:39.526 --> 18:43.852
As a matter of fact, it doesn't even come close to reality.

18:45.355 --> 18:49.561
And so I'm speaking this way to you, young people, because you have to understand.

18:52.987 --> 19:00.178
If you've ever seen a cattle truck pull up to a slaughterhouse and see those cattle, those cows in their change,

19:02.562 --> 19:06.368
You ever track blood of a deer that's been shot through the liver?

19:09.152 --> 19:13.058
Well, sinners can do far more damage to you.

19:14.320 --> 19:22.131
So please, please, when we study the book of Proverbs, I'm not here because I just like teaching children.

19:23.053 --> 19:29.362
I'm here because this is a matter, a severe matter, a serious matter.

19:30.434 --> 19:31.575
and you need to pay attention.

19:31.676 --> 19:34.018
We're going to see that in the next verses.

19:34.098 --> 19:37.082
Look at verse 24 that we'll study in the next lesson.

19:38.043 --> 19:43.089
Now therefore my sons, listen to me and pay attention to the words of my mouth.

19:44.231 --> 19:44.511
Why?

19:44.892 --> 19:45.693
It's life or death.

19:46.614 --> 19:47.315
All right, let's pray.

19:50.018 --> 19:52.000
Father, thank you for your word.

19:53.762 --> 19:56.786
Please Lord, through your spirit,

19:59.874 --> 20:10.044
that those who hear might not just be influenced for good, but renewed and transformed for a life of good.

20:11.625 --> 20:25.438
To pray, O God, that if there's anyone listening who does not know Christ, that they would run to Him, as to the only Savior, the only hope, the only light.

20:25.478 --> 20:29.202
In Jesus' name, amen.

20:31.394 --> 20:32.051
God Bless.

